<% layout('layouts/main.layout') %>

<% block('subTitle', 'Tutorial & Guide') %>

<section class="tutorial-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="tutorial-header text-center mb-5">
      <h1 class="section-title animate__animated" data-animation="animate__fadeIn">Tutorial & Guide</h1>
      <p class="section-subtitle animate__animated" data-animation="animate__fadeIn animate__delay-1s"> Learn how to use our platform with these easy-to-follow guides </p>
    </div>

    <div class="tutorial-tabs-container">
      <ul class="nav nav-tabs tutorial-tabs" id="tutorialTabs" role="tablist">
        <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
          <button class="nav-link active" id="basic-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#basic-content" type="button" role="tab" aria-controls="basic-content" aria-selected="true"> Install ModHeader </button>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
          <button class="nav-link" id="redeem-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#redeem-content" type="button" role="tab" aria-controls="redeem-content" aria-selected="false"> Redeem Code </button>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
          <button class="nav-link" id="usage-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#usage-content" type="button" role="tab" aria-controls="usage-content" aria-selected="false"> How to Use </button>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="tab-content tutorial-content" id="tutorialTabsContent">
        <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="basic-content" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="basic-tab">
          <div class="tutorial-card">
            <h2>Install ModHeader on Your Browser</h2>

            <h3>Step 1</h3>
            <p>Open your browser and search for the ModHeader Extension.</p>
            <div class="tutorial-img-container">
              <img src="images/modheader/step1.png" alt="Step 1 - Searching for ModHeader Extension" class="img-fluid tutorial-img" loading="lazy">
            </div>

            <h3>Step 2</h3>
            <p>Install the ModHeader Extension.</p>
            <div class="tutorial-img-container">
              <img src="images/modheader/step2.png" alt="Step 2 - Installing ModHeader" class="img-fluid tutorial-img" loading="lazy">
            </div>

            <h3>Step 3</h3>
            <p>Once installed, you should see a screen like this, indicating the installation is complete.</p>
            <div class="tutorial-img-container">
              <img src="images/modheader/step3.png" alt="Step 3 - Post-installation Screen" class="img-fluid tutorial-img" loading="lazy">
            </div>

            <div class="tutorial-note">
              <strong>Note:</strong> Be cautious when using ModHeader. Avoid modifying critical headers.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tab-pane fade" id="redeem-content" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="redeem-tab">
          <div class="tutorial-card">
            <h2>Redeem Your Token to Get the Config</h2>
            <p>Ensure you have received a token from us.</p>
            <h3>Example Token:</h3>
            <pre>2025-01-01-blueband-1234-01</pre>

            <h3>Step 1</h3>
            <p>Go to the service page and select Safe Exam Browser.</p>
            <div class="tutorial-img-container">
              <img src="images/redeem/step1.png" alt="Step 1 - Selecting Safe Exam Browser" class="img-fluid tutorial-img" loading="lazy">
            </div>

            <h3>Step 2</h3>
            <p>Fill out the form with your token, config name, and upload the config.seb file.</p>
            <div class="tutorial-img-container">
              <img src="images/redeem/step2.png" alt="Step 2 - Filling Out the Form" class="img-fluid tutorial-img" loading="lazy">
            </div>

            <h3>Step 3</h3>
            <p>Click the Upload button and wait for a notification confirming the config creation.</p>
            <div class="tutorial-img-container">
              <img src="images/redeem/step3.png" alt="Step 3 - Success Notification" class="img-fluid tutorial-img" loading="lazy">
            </div>

            <h3>Step 4</h3>
            <p>Download the generated config.seb file.</p>

            <div class="tutorial-note">
              <strong>Note:</strong> Tokens can only be used once. Handle them carefully.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tab-pane fade" id="usage-content" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="usage-tab">
          <div class="tutorial-card">
            <h2>How to Use the Config</h2>
            <p>Make sure you have downloaded the JSON file after redeeming your token.</p>

            <h3>Step 1</h3>
            <p>Open the ModHeader extension in your browser.</p>
            <div class="tutorial-img-container">
              <img src="images/usage/step1.png" alt="Step 1 - Opening ModHeader" class="img-fluid tutorial-img" loading="lazy">
            </div>

            <h3>Step 2</h3>
            <p>Follow the steps shown below.</p>
            <div class="tutorial-img-container">
              <img src="images/usage/step2.png" alt="Step 2 - Using ModHeader" class="img-fluid tutorial-img" loading="lazy">
              <img src="images/usage/step3.png" alt="Step 2 - Using ModHeader (import)" class="img-fluid tutorial-img" loading="lazy">
            </div>

            <h3>Step 3</h3>
            <p>After loading the JSON file, your ModHeader should look like this. Check all the boxes.</p>
            <div class="tutorial-img-container">
              <img src="images/usage/step4.png" alt="Step 3 - ModHeader Configuration" class="img-fluid tutorial-img" loading="lazy">
            </div>

            <pre>Now, open your Quiz/Exam page and refresh it.</pre>
            <pre>
              <h3>Congratulations! You can now take the quiz without using Safe Exam Browser.</h3>
            </pre>

            <div class="tutorial-note">
              <strong>Note:</strong> Be cautious when using ModHeader. Avoid modifying critical headers.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>